<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1386,2032]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1580,1606]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Recognized by the distinctively long, dense, erect or suberect, deep brown simple setae covering the dorsal surface of the body (
<figureCitation box="[620,732,1619,1645]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1818,1842]" captionTargetBox="[343,1230,403,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[340,1248,390,1792]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Habitus views of Pherolepis spp. 1. aenescens (male); 2. aenescens (female); 3. amplus (male); 4. amplus (female); 5. kiritshenkoi (male); 6. longipilus (male); 7. longipilus (female); 8. nigrinus (male); 9. nigrinus (female); 10. robustus (male); 11. robustus (female)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191188/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Figs. 
<number box="[686,732,1619,1645]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="6.7">6, 7</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[744,820,1619,1645]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 42" captionStartId="12.[151,270,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[184,1407,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[184,1409,197,1908]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 42. Scanning electron micrographs of morphological structures of P. longipilus (male): 37. Lateral view of head; 38. Scent-gland evaporatory area; 39. Simple setae on scutellum; 40. Simple setae on hemelytron. 41 – 42. Parempodia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191194/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<number box="[744,820,1619,1645]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="39.4">39, 40</number>
</figureCitation>
), the shining sericeous setae densely scattered on the proximal 
<number box="[268,283,1658,1684]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[293,306,1658,1684]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="3.0">3</number>
of hemelytron, the yellow-brown hemelytron, the castaneous head, pronotum and scutellum. Most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kulik" authorityName="Kulik" box="[352,553,1696,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Pherolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplus">
<emphasis box="[352,473,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. amplus</emphasis>
Kulik
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[571,692,1696,1722]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1818,1842]" captionTargetBox="[343,1230,403,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[340,1248,390,1792]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Habitus views of Pherolepis spp. 1. aenescens (male); 2. aenescens (female); 3. amplus (male); 4. amplus (female); 5. kiritshenkoi (male); 6. longipilus (male); 7. longipilus (female); 8. nigrinus (male); 9. nigrinus (female); 10. robustus (male); 11. robustus (female)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191188/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Figs. 
<number box="[643,692,1696,1722]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="3.4">3, 4</number>
</figureCitation>
) in size and coloration of dorsum, but distinguished by the structure of male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[473,615,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURES 43 – 48" captionStartId="13.[151,269,928,952]" captionTargetBox="[236,1424,218,891]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 43 – 48. Pherolepis longipilus sp. nov.: 43 – 47. Male genitalia (scale = 0.10 mm): 43. Vesica; 44. Left paramere; 45. Left paramere, apical view; 46. Right paramere; 47. Phallotheca. 48. Female genitalia (scale = 0.20 mm), dorsal view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191195/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Figs. 
<number box="[540,615,1735,1761]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="45.0" valueMax="47.0" valueMin="43.0">43–47</number>
</figureCitation>
) and the presence of extremely long simple setae (
<figureCitation box="[1208,1397,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 42" captionStartId="12.[151,270,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[184,1407,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[184,1409,197,1908]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 42. Scanning electron micrographs of morphological structures of P. longipilus (male): 37. Lateral view of head; 38. Scent-gland evaporatory area; 39. Simple setae on scutellum; 40. Simple setae on hemelytron. 41 – 42. Parempodia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191194/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Figs. 
<number box="[1274,1397,1735,1761]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="38.695" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="37.39">37, 39–40</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1386,2032]" box="[197,944,1773,1800]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,342,1773,1799]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Description</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis box="[357,417,1774,1799]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[433,506,1774,1800]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1818,1842]" captionTargetBox="[343,1230,403,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[340,1248,390,1792]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Habitus views of Pherolepis spp. 1. aenescens (male); 2. aenescens (female); 3. amplus (male); 4. amplus (female); 5. kiritshenkoi (male); 6. longipilus (male); 7. longipilus (female); 8. nigrinus (male); 9. nigrinus (female); 10. robustus (male); 11. robustus (female)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191188/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Fig. 
<number box="[488,506,1774,1800]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
): Macropterous, oval, medium-sized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1386,2032]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Coloration: General coloration yellowish brown or brown, without distinctive colored markings on dorsum; head, pronotum, exposed part of mesoscutum and scutellum castaneous to almost black; membrane fumose, without spots; eyes dark brown with outer margin reddish; antennal segment I and proximal half of segment II dirty yellow, distal half yellow-brown to castaneous, segment III and IV castaneous to black; clypeus and buccula reddish brown; labium yellowish brown; coxae and trochanter pale-yellow, femora and tibiae pale-brown, tarsal segment III blackish brown; abdomen dark brown.</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191194/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" targetBox="[184,1407,197,1907]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1942,2035]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,350,1942,1966]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">FIGURES 37–42.</emphasis>
