</caption>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1438,1032,2025]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Surface and Vestiture: Dorsal surface of body covered densely with two 
<typeStatus box="[1074,1137,1032,1058]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">types</typeStatus>
of setae, distinctly long, erect or suberect, simple setae (
<figureCitation box="[535,727,1071,1097]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 42" captionStartId="12.[151,270,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[184,1407,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[184,1409,197,1908]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 42. Scanning electron micrographs of morphological structures of P. longipilus (male): 37. Lateral view of head; 38. Scent-gland evaporatory area; 39. Simple setae on scutellum; 40. Simple setae on hemelytron. 41 – 42. Parempodia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191194/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figs. 
<number box="[604,727,1071,1097]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="38.695" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="37.39">37, 39–40</number>
</figureCitation>
) and decumbent or appressed, flattened, shining sericeous setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1438,1032,2025]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Structure: 
<emphasis box="[327,390,1148,1173]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[412,506,1148,1174]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 42" captionStartId="12.[151,270,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[184,1407,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[184,1409,197,1908]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 42. Scanning electron micrographs of morphological structures of P. longipilus (male): 37. Lateral view of head; 38. Scent-gland evaporatory area; 39. Simple setae on scutellum; 40. Simple setae on hemelytron. 41 – 42. Parempodia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191194/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[473,506,1148,1174]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="37.0">37</number>
</figureCitation>
): Triangular in frontal view and transverse in dorsal view, weakly convex posteriorly; vertex and frons moderately inclined, densely covered with two 
<typeStatus box="[1057,1119,1187,1213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">types</typeStatus>
of setae mentioned above, posterior margin of vertex forming a complete, weakly rounded carina; frons and clypeus distinctly protrudent, easily visible in dorsal view; mandibular and maxillary plates, and buccula covered with sparse, recumbent, simple setae; labium elongate, almost reaching posterior margin of hind trochanter; eyes broadly ovoid; antennal segment I short and stout, narrow at base, segment II long, tubular and weakly curved; segment III equal to segment IV in diameter and length, more slender than segment II. 
<emphasis box="[1214,1301,1380,1405]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotum broad, weakly tumidiform, anterior and posterior lobes not demarcated, posterolateral angles rounded, posterior margin slightly concave; mesoscutum broadly exposed, weakly declining; scutellum slightly swollen mesially; hemelytron broad, clavus weakly elevated along the claval commissure; cuneus broadly triangular, moderately declining; veins of membrane indistinct; femora stout and somewhat flattened, tibiae cylindrical and straight, with two rows of black short spicules; tarsal segment I and II subequal in length, segment III about two times length of segment II; claws distinctly curved, slightly broadened basally, pulvilli absent, parempodia lamellate, recurved, and convergent apically. 
<emphasis box="[967,1083,1651,1676]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Relatively stout and broad, generally covered with recumbent, pale simple setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1438,1032,2025]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[386,535,1728,1754]" captionStart="FIGURES 43 – 48" captionStartId="13.[151,269,928,952]" captionTargetBox="[236,1424,218,891]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 43 – 48. Pherolepis longipilus sp. nov.: 43 – 47. Male genitalia (scale = 0.10 mm): 43. Vesica; 44. Left paramere; 45. Left paramere, apical view; 46. Right paramere; 47. Phallotheca. 48. Female genitalia (scale = 0.20 mm), dorsal view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191195/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figs. 
<number box="[455,535,1728,1754]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="45.0" valueMax="47.0" valueMin="43.0">43–47</number>
</figureCitation>
): Vesica typically L-shaped, with a large, flattened, spinelike projection on shaft, near apex with a fingerlike process, apex of vesica with broad membrane (
<figureCitation box="[1102,1190,1767,1793]" captionStart="FIGURES 43 – 48" captionStartId="13.[151,269,928,952]" captionTargetBox="[236,1424,218,891]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 43 – 48. Pherolepis longipilus sp. nov.: 43 – 47. Male genitalia (scale = 0.10 mm): 43. Vesica; 44. Left paramere; 45. Left paramere, apical view; 46. Right paramere; 47. Phallotheca. 48. Female genitalia (scale = 0.20 mm), dorsal view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191195/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[1157,1190,1767,1793]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
); left paramere boatshaped, hypophysis elongate, sensory lobe blunt (
<figureCitation box="[738,882,1805,1831]" captionStart="FIGURES 43 – 48" captionStartId="13.[151,269,928,952]" captionTargetBox="[236,1424,218,891]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 43 – 48. Pherolepis longipilus sp. nov.: 43 – 47. Male genitalia (scale = 0.10 mm): 43. Vesica; 44. Left paramere; 45. Left paramere, apical view; 46. Right paramere; 47. Phallotheca. 48. Female genitalia (scale = 0.20 mm), dorsal view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191195/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figs. 
<number box="[805,882,1805,1831]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="44.45">44, 45</number>
</figureCitation>
); right paramere leaflike (
<figureCitation box="[1190,1279,1805,1831]" captionStart="FIGURES 43 – 48" captionStartId="13.[151,269,928,952]" captionTargetBox="[236,1424,218,891]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 43 – 48. Pherolepis longipilus sp. nov.: 43 – 47. Male genitalia (scale = 0.10 mm): 43. Vesica; 44. Left paramere; 45. Left paramere, apical view; 46. Right paramere; 47. Phallotheca. 48. Female genitalia (scale = 0.20 mm), dorsal view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191195/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[1246,1279,1805,1831]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="46.0">46</number>
</figureCitation>
); phallotheca elongate, apex weakly curved (
<figureCitation box="[515,603,1844,1870]" captionStart="FIGURES 43 – 48" captionStartId="13.[151,269,928,952]" captionTargetBox="[236,1424,218,891]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 43 – 48. Pherolepis longipilus sp. nov.: 43 – 47. Male genitalia (scale = 0.10 mm): 43. Vesica; 44. Left paramere; 45. Left paramere, apical view; 46. Right paramere; 47. Phallotheca. 48. Female genitalia (scale = 0.20 mm), dorsal view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191195/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number box="[570,603,1844,1870]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="47.0">47</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1438,1032,2025]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
